27/06/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A UN court in Kosovo on Friday (25 June) sentenced an ethnic Albanian from southern Serbia to 12 years in prison for kidnapping and extortion. Shefqet Musliu was a senior figure in the now disbanded Albanian Liberation Army of Presevo, Medvedja and Bujanovac. He is also on the US list of 22 individuals who threaten peace in the Western Balkans. (AFP - 25/06/04)
